post_text: Due to the recent spike in COVID-19 cases in the San Antonio area, Lackland ISD will close all campuses and district operations for the week of June 29-July 3. In the season of giving, we are asking for new toy donations. All toys donated will be given to children at the San Antonio Military Medical Center.

We will hold our 11th Annual Toy Drive December 1, 2017 - December 15, 2017. SAMC is requesting toys and new books for the Children who will spend Christmas in the hospital. The gifts will be distributed on Christmas Eve. Gifts should be unwrapped and marked Male or Female with appropriate age. Gifts may be turned in at the District office between 8:00 AM - 4:30 PM. Please support our efforts and donate. Thank You!

post_text: “We don’t panic…we perform,” said Mr. Rodriguez, Lackland ISD’s Food Service Manager, after learning that all student lunches would need to be expedited last Friday due to the impending storm. This motto definitely describes our food service workers and it certainly would describe the professionalism and performance of all Lackland ISD employees last week. A big thank you to all staff for going the “extra mile”. A special thanks to our PTSO Board for jumping in and helping---we are so grateful for all that you do for our students, families, staff and district!

post_text: The recent unprecedented destruction to the Gulf Coast region has left millions of people in need. Lackland ISD is launching an effort to provide relief for those families that are hurting. The first step in this effort is a food drive in support of the San Antonio Food Bank which has been providing aide to those in need of food and supplies and currently desperately need your donations. There are food collection boxes set up at the district, high school and elementary offices as well as in Mrs. Duron’s and Mr. Poludniak’s rooms. You can bring your nonperishable food donations to those locations between now and September 15th. Millions of Texans now face unthinkable uncertainty in the wake of Harvey but together we can make a difference.

post_text: Traditionally, the end of the school year is a season of transitions for our military families. To alleviate potential stressors related to these transitions we want to remind you of the supports available through our JBSA School Liaison Officer, Ms. Lori Phipps at lori.phipps@usaf.mil and our Military Student Transition Consultant (MSTC), Mrs. Aimee Carrasco at carrasco.a@lacklandisd.net. Both are available throughout the school year and summer months to support your transitioning needs. We are reintroducing to most and introducing to some, the Military Student Transition Consultant for Lackland ISD, Mrs. Aimee Carrasco.

Congratulations to Dr. Kristina Vidaurri! On April 19th, 2017, Ms. Vidaurri was confirmed with her doctoral degree in education, from UTSA, and will officially graduate in May.

Dr. Vidaurri wears many hats for the district, but it is so fitting that she is Lackland ISD’s AVID Program Director. AVID, or Advancement Via Individual Determination, so aptly describes her commitment to student success, as well as her own. Her educational attainment highlights that the “sky’s the limit” for all eagles! We are so proud of you Dr. Vidaurri!

post_text: Future Ready. It is more than a slogan, it is Lackland ISD’s commitment to our students. On March 23, 2017, over 120 students from both the elementary and secondary campus of Lackland ISD attended JBSA – Lackland’s Education Fair. With more than 45 colleges and universities in attendance, students were able to engage recruiters from all over the United States. Many of our elementary students learned about vast educational opportunities available at trade schools, community colleges, and traditional four-year university. They also learned about the courses they need to begin taking in middle school to ensure they are prepared for their field of interest. Meanwhile, many of our high school students asked the academic representatives questions about degree programs, campus life, method of instruction and, of course, tuition. We would like to thank all of the colleges and universities in attendance, as well as the JBSA – Lackland Education Services Division for partnering with us and helping play a pivotal role ensuring that our students are Future Ready.

post_text: Tammy Schultz serves as an instructional aide for our high school. As an instructional aide, Mrs. Schultz provides classroom support for students in our special education and general education programs. Mrs. Schultz’s responsibilities include learning the curriculum across grade levels, tracking classroom assignments, and monitoring assignment due dates in several classes, which requires a great deal of preparation and organizational skills. Mrs. Shultz can also be counted on to help in other areas when needed, most recently helping the transportation department transport a student with special needs. We are proud to recognize Tammy Schultz as one of Fall 2016 Above & Beyond award winners.

During the beginning of the school year, he worked many extra hours assembling furniture and setting up classrooms to ensure that the schools where ready for our students. Teachers and staff appreciate his help and enthusiasm here at Lackland ISD. We are proud to recognize Ricardo Rodriguez as one of our Fall 2016 Above & Beyond award winners.

post_text: Stephanie Lawrence serves as a 3rd Grade teacher for our Elementary School. Stephanie has been teaching at Lackland ISD for 16 years. During these 16 years, she has consistently gone above-and-beyond in her commitment to teaching our students. She comes to work early, stays late, and occasionally comes in to work on weekends to make sure that she is doing her very best. She is kind and considerate and is always surrounded by her students. Parents are also drawn to her, often contacting her even when their child has gone on to the next grade or different school. We are proud to recognize Stephanie Lawrence as one of our Fall 2016 Above & Beyond award winners.

post_text: Victoria Payne serves as one of our 4th grade teachers for our Elementary School. Ms. Payne is an outstanding teacher who goes above-and-beyond in teaching her students. Pryor to teaching, Ms. Payne worked in the corporate world where she developed an expertise in the areas of marketing, photography, and web design. She uses her knowledge and experience to develop lessons that are interesting and highly interactive. In addition, Ms. Payne takes great care in ensuring that all her students fully comprehend the lessons she is teaching in her classroom. We are proud to recognize Victoria Payne as one of our Fall 2016 Above & Beyond award winners.
